Americans, very independent, they were already

00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:59.100
voting for their own magistrates and stuff,
which was not typically English, but John

00:16:59.100 --> 00:17:04.010
Winthrop learned early on that all these guys
who are risking their whole lives to live

00:17:04.010 --> 00:17:08.660
in the wilderness being given their way, they
got pretty upset. So they started taking the,

00:17:08.660 --> 00:17:12.669
you know, advice of the freemen. That's what
they call them. You signed an oath and that

00:17:12.669 --> 00:17:18.760
made you a freeman and you're going to have
a vote, the first democratic voting in the

00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:25.610
area. So, after the king got the petition,
he sent Andros (ph) down. He had him take

00:17:25.610 --> 00:17:32.409
over the whole New England. They threw out
the Charter, which they had since they landed,

00:17:32.409 --> 00:17:37.279
and arrested all the people from Ipswich who
were involved in it, but it's—-so it was

00:17:37.279 --> 00:17:43.850
like all the selectmen, all the freeman, the
preachers, all the main important men of the

00:17:43.850 --> 00:17:47.450
town were arrested and had to go before the
king and write an apology. And they all did

00:17:47.450 --> 00:17:53.140
but Sam Appleton, who was 68 at that time
and he refused to do it and he was jailed

00:17:53.140 --> 00:17:59.470
until Andros (ph) was finally thrown out and
then William and Mary took over. In England,

00:17:59.470 --> 00:18:03.590
there was a new government, so they stopped
chasing after their colonies for a little

00:18:03.590 --> 00:18:10.000
